race.comment: ZEMGRINDA (5) didn't do a bad job when fourth last start over 1000m at Seymour, beaten 2.5 lengths. That followed a win at Kilmore the start prior. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. MARILYN'S EDGE (10) finished 4.5 lengths adrift in eighth last time at Caulfield Heath after being in the firing line on the corner in a disappointing performance. Faces an easier assignment so she is a major player. KING INCANTO (4) scored two back at Wangaratta but was below his best last time when fifth over 1500m at Albury. Should be competitive in this suitable race. BRITISH POET (2) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 12 lengths when tenth in a 1400m contest at Geelong five weeks ago after being in contention on the corner. Has the class to find the winners' list. MOJO MUSIC (13) is on the back-up after a huge win at Bong Bong and while this is a little tougher, he's drawn to get his chance to measure up.
